<subSubSection box="[151,1107,474,496]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1107,474,496]" box="[151,1107,474,496]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,474,496]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Type taxon</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lyman, 1869)" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[283,653,474,496]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[283,495,474,496]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiodia pulchella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." box="[508,647,474,496]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="309 - 354" part="1" refId="ref50617" refString="Lyman, T. (1869) Preliminary Report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredge in deep water between Cuba and the Florida Reef. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 1, 309 - 354." title="Preliminary Report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredge in deep water between Cuba and the Florida Reef" type="journal article" year="1869">Lyman, 1869</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, originally described as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[900,1101,474,496]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[900,1101,474,496]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiura pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,535,992]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,535,560]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Disc with scales dorsally and ventrally. Radial shields contiguous for almost their entire length or separated proximally by up to four scales. Two lateral oral papillae, distal slightly larger, circular or triangular. One to two tentacle scales. Three to four arm spines, dorsal usually longer (
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill, A. E." box="[986,1142,607,632]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin from the Laboratories of Natural History of the State University of Iowa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 88" part="5" refId="ref55183" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1899 a) Report on the Ophiuroidea collected by the Bahama expedition in 1893. Bulletin from the Laboratories of Natural History of the State University of Iowa, 5, 1 - 88." title="Report on the Ophiuroidea collected by the Bahama expedition in 1893" type="journal article" year="1899">Verrill 1899a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[1157,1316,607,632]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="623 - 694" part="12" refId="ref54585" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1962) The shallow water amphiurid brittle stars (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea) of Florida. Bulletin of Marine Science, 12, 623 - 694." title="The shallow water amphiurid brittle stars (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea) of Florida" type="journal article" year="1962">Thomas 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tommasi, L. R." journalOrPublisher="Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 146" part="20" refId="ref54902" refString="Tommasi, L. R. (1970) Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas. Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 20, 1 - 146." title="Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas" type="journal article" year="1970">Tommasi 1970</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,535,992]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,679,704]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[342,465,680,704]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[342,465,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described for some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forbes" authorityYear="1843" box="[861,973,680,704]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,973,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with different jaw characteristics (
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill, A. E." journalOrPublisher="Bulletin from the Laboratories of Natural History of the State University of Iowa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 88" part="5" refId="ref55183" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1899 a) Report on the Ophiuroidea collected by the Bahama expedition in 1893. Bulletin from the Laboratories of Natural History of the State University of Iowa, 5, 1 - 88." title="Report on the Ophiuroidea collected by the Bahama expedition in 1893" type="journal article" year="1899">Verrill 1899a</bibRefCitation>
). The number, shape, size, and distribution of lateral oral papillae were essential to assign an additional three groups to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forbes" authorityYear="1843" box="[265,377,752,776]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[265,377,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[393,534,752,776]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,534,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[550,680,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[550,676,752,776]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Amphiodia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[736,870,752,776]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphioplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[736,870,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphioplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[1012,1146,752,776]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphioplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1012,1146,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphioplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has three or more lateral oral papillae, the other genera only have two lateral oral papillae, whose shape and size differentiate them. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forbes" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,263,824,848]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,263,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a buccal scale higher up on the jaw, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[721,863,824,848]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,863,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a much-widened distal papilla, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[1313,1436,824,848]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a slightly larger distal papilla that may be circular or more triangular. Currently, 35 species are accepted in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stohr et al. 2016)" authorityName="Stohr et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[151,492,895,920]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,896,920]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Amphiodia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A." box="[289,484,895,920]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="0164562" part="11" refId="ref54292" refString="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. (2016) Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars. PLoS ONE, 11, e 0164562. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0164562" title="Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars" type="journal article" year="2016">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[359,409,896,920]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with five recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[782,850,895,920]" name="Brazil" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M." box="[866,1146,895,920]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 21" part="3447" refId="ref44247" refString="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M. (2012) A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters. Zootaxa, 3447, 1 - 21." title="A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters" type="journal article" year="2012">Barboza &amp; Borges 2012</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque, Campos-Creasey &amp; Guille, 2001" authorityName="Albuquerque, Campos-Creasey &amp; Guille" authorityYear="2001" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="habilis">
<emphasis box="[1166,1275,896,920]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. habilis</emphasis>
Albuquerque, Campos-Creasey &amp; Guille, 2001
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Von Martens, 1867)" authorityName="Von Martens" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Von Martens" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[557,974,932,957]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="planispina">
<emphasis box="[557,713,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. planispina</emphasis>
(Von Martens, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lyman, 1869)" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[992,1323,932,957]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[992,1134,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. pulchella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." box="[1155,1315,932,957]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="309 - 354" part="1" refId="ref50617" refString="Lyman, T. (1869) Preliminary Report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredge in deep water between Cuba and the Florida Reef. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 1, 309 - 354." title="Preliminary Report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredge in deep water between Cuba and the Florida Reef" type="journal article" year="1869">Lyman, 1869</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lutken, 1859)" authorityName="Lutken" authorityYear="1859" baseAuthorityName="Lutken" baseAuthorityYear="1859" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="riisei">
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. riisei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lutken, C. F." bookContentInfo="95 pp." box="[158,310,967,992]" journalOrPublisher="Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskabs Skrifter, Copenhagen" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="177 - 271" refId="ref50491" refString="Lutken, C. F. (1859) Additamenta ad historiam Ophiuridarum: Beskrivelser af nye eller hidtil kun ufuldstaendigt kjendte Arter af Slangestjerner. Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskabs Skrifter, Copenhagen, 95 pp. [pp. 177 - 271]" title="Additamenta ad historiam Ophiuridarum: Beskrivelser af nye eller hidtil kun ufuldstaendigt kjendte Arter af Slangestjerner" type="book chapter" year="1859">Lütken, 1859</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="H. L. Clark, 1918" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1918" box="[373,697,967,992]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="trychna">
<emphasis box="[373,490,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. trychna</emphasis>
H. L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, H. L." box="[562,697,967,992]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="263 - 338" part="62" refId="ref46530" refString="Clark, H. L. (1918) Brittle-stars, new and old. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 62, 263 - 338." title="Brittle-stars, new and old" type="journal article" year="1918">Clark, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
